cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper discusses a new size-independent indicator of scientific journal prestige that takes into account the closeness of the citing and cited journals using the cosine of the angle between their cocitation profiles. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), and digital libraries (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper's focus on measuring scientific journal prestige could also fit within the category of computers and society (cs.CY).
